WEBVTT

00:02.168 --> 00:03.461
-<i> HOT IN CLEVELAND</i> IS RECORDED

00:03.545 --> 00:05.588
IN FRONT
OF A LIVE STUDIO AUDIENCE.

00:05.672 --> 00:07.632
- OKAY, ELKA, WE HAVE A LOT
OF FUND-RAISERS THIS WEEK

00:07.716 --> 00:08.925
FOR YOUR CITY COUNCIL CAMPAIGN.

00:09.008 --> 00:10.468
SO THERE'S
THE BIG SILENT AUCTION HERE

00:10.552 --> 00:12.262
ON SATURDAY NIGHT,
AND THEN TOMORROW,

00:12.345 --> 00:13.888
YOU'RE SPEAKING
AT THE IRISH-AMERICAN CLUB.

00:13.972 --> 00:16.224
- I HAVE THE PERFECT JOKE
TO OPEN WITH.

00:16.306 --> 00:18.059
- WHAT IS IT?

00:18.143 --> 00:20.270
- WHY WASN'T JESUS BORN
IN IRELAND?

00:20.353 --> 00:21.604
- WHY?

00:21.688 --> 00:23.440
- HE COULDN'T FIND
THREE WISE MEN

00:23.523 --> 00:25.650
OR A VIRGIN.

00:29.487 --> 00:32.073
- NO, YOU'RE NOT TELLING
THAT JOKE,

00:32.156 --> 00:33.950
BUT I DO HAVE A CLEAN ONE
FOR YOU.

00:34.033 --> 00:36.619
WHAT'S IRISH
AND STAYS OUTSIDE?

00:36.703 --> 00:38.955
PADDY O'FURNITURE.

00:39.038 --> 00:41.958
[cricket chirping]

00:42.041 --> 00:44.169
OH, THAT STUPID CRICKET.

00:44.252 --> 00:46.463
HOW COME IT ONLY CHIRPS
WHEN I TELL A JOKE?

00:46.546 --> 00:49.716
- SOMETHING'S GOT TO FILL
THE DEAD AIR.

00:49.799 --> 00:51.968
- I JUST GOT A TEXT
FROM J.J.

00:52.051 --> 00:54.304
I AM FINALLY GONNA MEET
MY YOUNG, HOT SCREENWRITER.

00:54.387 --> 00:55.263
HE'S COMING OVER TOMORROW.

00:55.346 --> 00:57.682
- IS HE REALLY A JUNIOR
AT CLEVELAND STATE?

00:57.766 --> 01:00.643
- YES, MY AGENT SAYS
THAT DOING A STUDENT FILM

01:00.727 --> 01:02.187
IS A BRILLIANT MOVE.

01:02.270 --> 01:04.772
NOW BUZZFEED IS CALLING ME
HIP AND EDGY.

01:04.855 --> 01:08.735
- IF YOUR HIPS WERE ANY EDGIER,
THEY'D CUT THROUGH YOUR PANTS.

01:08.818 --> 01:11.988
- OH, THANK YOU.

01:13.364 --> 01:15.200
- I NEED HELP.

01:15.283 --> 01:16.951
I'M MEETING MITCH IN AN HOUR,
AND I CAN'T DECIDE WHAT TO WEAR,

01:17.035 --> 01:18.953
AND I HAVE TO LOOK PERFECT,

01:19.037 --> 01:20.830
BECAUSE I'M FINALLY
GONNA TELL HIM

01:20.914 --> 01:23.041
HOW I FEEL ABOUT HIM.

01:23.124 --> 01:24.959
OF COURSE I KNOW
YOU'RE ALL GOING TO SAY

01:25.043 --> 01:27.337
I SHOULD JUST RELAX
AND BE MYSELF.

01:27.420 --> 01:30.757
[cricket chirping]

01:30.840 --> 01:34.093
OH, MY GOD,
MELANIE'S CRICKET'S RIGHT.

01:34.177 --> 01:36.596
BEING MYSELF WITH MEN
NEVER WORKS.

01:36.679 --> 01:38.681
MAYBE I SHOULD TRY
BEING THE OPPOSITE OF ME.

01:38.765 --> 01:39.891
NORMALLY ON A DATE,

01:39.974 --> 01:41.976
I'D DRINK ALCOHOL
FOR COURAGE

01:42.060 --> 01:44.020
AND SHOW AS MUCH LEG
AS POSSIBLE,

01:44.103 --> 01:48.483
SO TONIGHT,
I'M GOING TO NOT DRINK AT ALL

01:48.566 --> 01:51.152
AND WEAR LONG PANTS.

01:51.236 --> 01:53.196
[all gasp]

01:54.781 --> 01:57.325
[upbeat music]

01:57.408 --> 01:59.661
- ♪ BA-BA, BA-BA ♪

01:59.744 --> 02:02.831
♪ BA-BA, BA-BA ♪

02:02.914 --> 02:04.374
♪ HEY! ♪

02:04.457 --> 02:05.667
{\an8}- SO, JOY, YOU SAID
YOU HAD SOMETHING IMPORTANT

02:05.750 --> 02:06.668
{\an8}YOU WANTED TO TELL ME?

02:06.751 --> 02:09.336
{\an8}- YES, YOU SEE--

02:09.419 --> 02:11.548
{\an8}COULD I JUST HAVE A SIP
OF YOUR MARTINI?

02:11.631 --> 02:13.049
{\an8}- OH, I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU WEREN'T DRINKING TONIGHT.

02:13.132 --> 02:15.176
{\an8}- OH, JUST A TINY SIP.

02:21.140 --> 02:25.228
{\an8}- DID YOU WANT TO TELL ME
YOU HAVE A DRINKING PROBLEM?

02:25.311 --> 02:28.022
{\an8}- NO.

02:28.106 --> 02:30.900
{\an8}MITCH, I'M JUST GONNA SAY IT.

02:30.984 --> 02:33.528
{\an8}I AM COMPLETELY
AND TOTALLY--

02:33.611 --> 02:36.281
{\an8}- HOLD THAT THOUGHT.
BAZ, HEY.

02:36.364 --> 02:38.032
{\an8}SORRY, JOY.
THIS IS MY OLD FRIEND BAZ.

02:38.116 --> 02:39.576
{\an8}BAZ, THIS IS JOY.
- HELLO.

02:39.659 --> 02:40.869
{\an8}- YOU'RE EARLY, MAN.
JUST GIVE ME ONE SECOND.

02:40.952 --> 02:42.579
{\an8}JOY WAS TELLING ME SOMETHING.

02:42.662 --> 02:46.040
{\an8}YOU WERE SAYING YOU'RE
COMPLETELY AND TOTALLY--WHAT?

02:46.124 --> 02:47.792
{\an8}- NEEDING TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

02:47.876 --> 02:51.713
{\an8}EXCUSE ME.

02:51.796 --> 02:53.756
{\an8}- HEY, I HOPE IT'S OKAY
I SAID YOU WERE MY OLD FRIEND.

02:53.840 --> 02:55.383
{\an8}I JUST DON'T WANT
ANYONE TO KNOW

02:55.466 --> 02:56.759
{\an8}THAT I HIRED
A DATING CONSULTANT.

02:56.843 --> 02:58.928
{\an8}I'M TERRIBLE WITH WOMEN,

02:59.012 --> 03:01.556
{\an8}ALTHOUGH I'VE BEEN WATCHING
A LOT OF ROMANTIC COMEDIES,

03:01.639 --> 03:03.808
{\an8}AND I'VE NOTICED
THAT MAKING A GRAND GESTURE

03:03.892 --> 03:05.268
{\an8}SEEMS TO DO THE TRICK.

03:05.351 --> 03:07.061
{\an8}- OKAY, FIRST OF ALL,
YOU'RE A MAN.

03:07.145 --> 03:10.273
YOU SHOULDN'T BE WATCHING
ROMANTIC COMEDIES.

03:10.356 --> 03:11.608
LET'S START SIMPLE.

03:11.691 --> 03:15.236
NOTICE ONE THING ABOUT HER
AND COMPLIMENT IT.

03:15.320 --> 03:18.197
YOU FIND ONE SPECIAL FEATURE
NO MAN HAS EVER MENTIONED.

03:18.281 --> 03:19.616
- I CAN DO THAT.

03:19.699 --> 03:21.743
- NEXT, ASK HER A QUESTION
ABOUT HERSELF

03:21.826 --> 03:24.412
AND THEN SEEM FASCINATED
BY THE ANSWER.

03:24.495 --> 03:27.123
HMM.

03:27.206 --> 03:28.958
both: HMM.

03:29.042 --> 03:30.585
- OKAY,
YOU SEE THAT PRETTY BLONDE

03:30.668 --> 03:33.087
OVER THERE AT THE BAR,
THE ONE SEPARATED FROM THE HERD?

03:33.171 --> 03:36.883
BE A COWBOY.
GO LASSO HER.

03:40.386 --> 03:41.971
OKAY, LET'S STOP.

03:44.557 --> 03:47.477
- MELANIE, IT'S ME.
IT'S A DISASTER.

03:47.560 --> 03:49.771
- DON'T WORRY, HONEY.
WE'RE ALL BEHIND YOU.

03:49.854 --> 03:51.731
- THANKS.
- NO, LITERALLY. TURN AROUND.

03:54.567 --> 03:56.152
- THANK GOD YOU'RE HERE.

03:56.235 --> 03:57.820
- WELL, WE THOUGHT
THINGS MIGHT NOT WORK OUT,

03:57.904 --> 03:59.447
SO WE HAVE
A BRILLIANT PLAN.

03:59.530 --> 04:03.326
- DEAR, YOU LOOK LIKE A WOMAN
OF REFINEMENT AND DISTINCTION.

04:03.409 --> 04:05.828
- THANK YOU, ELKA.
- IT DOESN'T SUIT YOU.

04:05.912 --> 04:07.205
HERE.
SNIP, SNIP.

04:27.934 --> 04:29.811
- WOULD YOU TELL MITCH
THAT I NEEDED TO LEAVE?

04:29.894 --> 04:30.603
- SURE, SURE.

04:30.687 --> 04:32.146
BUT CAN I JUST TELL YOU
ONE THING?

04:32.230 --> 04:34.399
YOU HAVE THE MOST BEAUTIFUL...

04:34.482 --> 04:36.359
- LEGS. YES, THANKS.
WHATEVER.

04:36.442 --> 04:39.028
- ACTUALLY,
I WAS GONNA SAY ELBOWS.

04:39.112 --> 04:42.031
YOUR ELBOWS ARE EXQUISITE.

04:42.115 --> 04:44.033
- REALLY?

04:44.117 --> 04:48.538
I DO USE A GRANULAR SCRUB.

04:48.621 --> 04:52.542
- A GRANULAR SCRUB.
HMM.

04:52.625 --> 04:55.545
SO, JOY, YOU MARRIED?
- NO.

04:55.628 --> 04:59.799
BUT THERE IS SOMEONE
I'M INTERESTED IN.

04:59.882 --> 05:00.925
- WHO, MITCH?

05:01.009 --> 05:03.094
- PRETTY OBVIOUS,
I SUPPOSE,

05:03.177 --> 05:04.595
THOUGH NOT TO HIM.

05:04.679 --> 05:06.389
- YOU KNOW, JOY,
MAYBE I CAN HELP.

05:06.472 --> 05:09.225
HOW ABOUT YOU AND I
GO OUT TO DINNER?

05:09.308 --> 05:11.269
I'LL FILL YOU IN ON EVERYTHING
MITCH LIKES IN A WOMAN.

05:11.352 --> 05:13.062
- YOU WOULD DO THAT FOR ME?

05:13.146 --> 05:16.566
- I WOULD DO ANYTHING
FOR THOSE ELBOWS.

05:16.649 --> 05:19.902
- [chuckles]
THEY ARE RATHER SOFT.

05:19.986 --> 05:21.696
- IT'S THE GRANULAR SCRUB.

05:21.779 --> 05:23.281
- [laughs]

05:26.159 --> 05:27.285
HOW'S TOMORROW NIGHT?

05:27.368 --> 05:29.370
- IT'S A DATE.
- I'LL SEE YOU THEN.

05:37.795 --> 05:39.464
- HOW'D IT GO?

05:39.547 --> 05:41.924
- WELL, YOUR TRICKS WORKED,
BUT I COULDN'T STAND HER.

05:42.008 --> 05:43.593
SHE'S WAY INTO ASTROLOGY,

05:43.676 --> 05:46.095
AND SHE TALKS
IN THIS AWFUL BABY TALK.

05:46.179 --> 05:47.430
SHE WANTED TO KNOW
WHAT SIGN I WAS

05:47.513 --> 05:49.766
BECAUSE APPARENTLY
HER NEW "WITTLE" KITTEN

05:49.849 --> 05:53.978
DOESN'T LIKE "AWIES."

05:54.062 --> 05:56.522
- OKAY, MOVING ON.
PICK ANOTHER ONE.

05:56.606 --> 05:59.108
- YOU KNOW,
I DON'T THINK I WANT TO.

05:59.192 --> 06:01.527
THE STRANGEST THING
HAPPENED.

06:01.611 --> 06:03.738
WHEN I LOOKED OVER
AND SAW YOU AND JOY LAUGHING,

06:03.821 --> 06:07.116
I THINK I FELT JEALOUS.

06:07.200 --> 06:09.452
- WHAT, ARE YOU SAYING
YOU WANT JOY?

06:09.535 --> 06:12.080
- I THINK I AM.

06:12.163 --> 06:13.539
- HERE'S WHAT YOU DO.

06:13.623 --> 06:15.750
YOU LET ME TAKE HER OUT
TO DINNER.

06:15.833 --> 06:20.129
I'LL FIND OUT
EVERYTHING SHE WANTS IN A MAN.

06:20.213 --> 06:21.923
- HI, MITCH.
- HI, ELKA.

06:22.006 --> 06:25.093
- GONNA INTRODUCE ME
TO YOUR HANDSOME FRIEND?

06:25.176 --> 06:27.261
- ELKA, THIS IS BAZ.

06:27.345 --> 06:28.805
BAZ, ELKA.
- HI.

06:28.888 --> 06:33.643
- HAS ANYONE EVER TOLD YOU
YOU HAVE GORGEOUS EARLOBES?

06:35.686 --> 06:37.647
- ACTUALLY, NO, I--

06:37.730 --> 06:39.816
HEY.

06:39.899 --> 06:41.943
YOU'RE GOOD.

06:43.611 --> 06:45.363
- NOW WATCH ME WALK AWAY.

06:53.204 --> 06:55.665
[doorbell chimes]

06:55.748 --> 06:56.833
- HI.

06:56.916 --> 06:59.377
- YOU'VE OBVIOUSLY GOT
THE WRONG HOUSE.

06:59.460 --> 07:01.587
NO ONE HERE
WOULD EVER ORDER A PIZZA.

07:01.671 --> 07:04.590
I MEAN, SOMETIMES WE GET ONE
JUST TO SNIFF IT,

07:04.674 --> 07:06.467
BUT THEN WE IMMEDIATELY
SQUIRT IT WITH WINDEX

07:06.551 --> 07:08.803
AND THROW IT OUT.

07:08.886 --> 07:10.513
WHY AM I TELLING YOU THIS?

07:10.596 --> 07:11.973
YOU PROBABLY
DON'T EVEN SPEAK ENGLISH.

07:12.056 --> 07:13.474
- I SPEAK ENGLISH.

07:13.558 --> 07:15.768
- OH, WELL, GOOD FOR YOU.
BUH-BYE.

07:20.231 --> 07:24.318
LOOK, I'M EXPECTING SOMEONE
FOR A VERY IMPORTANT MEETING.

07:24.402 --> 07:27.655
HE'S A YOUNG, HIP SCREENWRITER
WHO WROTE A BRILLIANT SCRIPT.

07:27.738 --> 07:31.742
- BRILLIANT?
- YES, THAT MEANS <i> MOLTO BENE.</i>

07:31.826 --> 07:34.203
ALTHOUGH
I'LL NEVER TELL HIM.

07:34.287 --> 07:36.330
I NEED TO BEND HIM
TO MY WILL,

07:36.414 --> 07:39.000
MOLD HIM
LIKE A PIECE OF MARBLE.

07:39.083 --> 07:42.545
- YOU CARVE MARBLE.
YOU MOLD CLAY.

07:42.628 --> 07:44.547
- I KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING.

07:44.630 --> 07:47.049
AFTER ALL,
WHICH ONE OF US SPEAKS ENGLISH?

07:47.133 --> 07:50.428
- I'M NOT SURE.

07:50.511 --> 07:51.721
MAYBE WE SHOULD START AGAIN.

07:51.804 --> 07:53.723
I'M J.J.,

07:53.806 --> 07:56.142
AND I HEAR
I'VE WRITTEN A BRILLIANT SCRIPT.

07:59.687 --> 08:02.523
- YOU'RE J.J.?
BUT YOU'RE NOT YOUNG AND HIP.

08:02.607 --> 08:05.193
YOU'RE--
HOW CAN I PUT THIS NICELY?

08:05.276 --> 08:09.071
YOU'RE OLD AND CLEVELAND-Y.

08:09.155 --> 08:10.448
- I WAS AFRAID
YOU WERE GOING TO BE

08:10.531 --> 08:12.283
A CRAZY HOLLYWOOD ACTRESS.

08:12.366 --> 08:14.869
- SO WE WERE BOTH WRONG.

08:14.952 --> 08:16.537
- SURE.

08:16.621 --> 08:19.248
I'M GUESSING THIS PIZZA'S
ALL FOR ME.

08:19.332 --> 08:21.709
- OH, I'LL SNIFF A SLICE.

08:21.792 --> 08:23.586
[sniffs]

08:23.669 --> 08:25.254
AH.

08:25.338 --> 08:27.340
JUST ONE.

08:30.843 --> 08:31.761
- HEY, THANKS FOR MAKING
THE COFFEE.

08:31.844 --> 08:32.929
- NO PROBLEM.

08:33.011 --> 08:34.388
SOMETHING TELLS ME
YOU LIKE HAVING PEOPLE

08:34.472 --> 08:36.140
DO THINGS FOR YOU.

08:36.224 --> 08:39.727
- I DO.
YOU GET ME.

08:42.020 --> 08:45.775
I'M ACTUALLY GLAD THAT YOU'RE
NOT SOME YOUNG COLLEGE HOTSHOT.

08:45.858 --> 08:47.443
OH, NOTHING GETS ME
MORE DEPRESSED

08:47.526 --> 08:52.073
THAN WHEN YOUNG PEOPLE
ARE GOOD AT THINGS.

08:52.156 --> 08:55.284
- WELL, I'M GLAD
YOU'RE PERFECT FOR THE ROLE.

08:55.368 --> 08:59.789
YOU'RE A GIFTED ACTRESS
AND A CONCERT PIANIST.

08:59.872 --> 09:02.667
- YEAH.

09:02.750 --> 09:05.586
UH, NOW MIGHT BE
A GOOD TIME TO MENTION

09:05.670 --> 09:08.005
THAT HOLLYWOOD ACTORS
ARE EXPECTED

09:08.089 --> 09:10.132
TO EMBELLISH THEIR RESUMES.

09:10.216 --> 09:12.009
- SO YOU DON'T PLAY THE PIANO?

09:12.093 --> 09:14.804
- MM, NOT EXCELLENTLY,

09:14.887 --> 09:18.724
BUT I AM REALLY GOOD
AT DOING BRILLIANT PIANO HANDS.

09:20.726 --> 09:21.477
- [laughs]

09:21.560 --> 09:23.479
NO, NO,
I NEED SOMEONE WHO CAN PLAY.

09:23.562 --> 09:24.730
YOU SEE, THIS CHARACTER
EXPRESSES HER EMOTIONS

09:24.814 --> 09:25.982
THROUGH MUSIC.

09:26.065 --> 09:28.276
- OH, OH, YOU WANT EMOTIONS?
HUH.

09:28.359 --> 09:30.361
ANGER.

09:31.362 --> 09:33.531
SAD.

09:35.283 --> 09:37.326
MISCHIEVOUS.

09:40.579 --> 09:41.998
- YEAH, I DON'T THINK
THIS IS GONNA WORK OUT.

09:42.081 --> 09:42.999
- NO, NO, NO.
LISTEN.

09:43.082 --> 09:45.334
I LOVE THIS SCRIPT,

09:45.418 --> 09:47.044
AND I LOVE
THE CHARACTER YOU CREATED.

09:47.128 --> 09:49.714
I WILL DO ANYTHING
TO PLAY THIS PART.

09:49.797 --> 09:53.301
- FINE, GET A PIANO HERE TODAY.
I'LL START TEACHING YOU TONIGHT.

09:53.384 --> 09:55.469
- OH, THANK YOU.
YOU WON'T REGRET IT.

09:55.553 --> 09:56.554
- YEAH.

09:56.637 --> 09:58.472
- HAPPY.

10:01.267 --> 10:04.186
- AND I LOVE THE WAY HE SMELLS
AND HIS GENEROSITY.

10:04.270 --> 10:06.272
I CAN'T STAND A CHEAP MAN.

10:06.355 --> 10:08.190
OH, AND HE'S NOT OBSESSED
WITH SPORTS.

10:08.274 --> 10:10.860
BUT I'M REALLY HOPING
TO FIND OUT WHAT HE LIKES.

10:10.943 --> 10:14.572
- WELL, MITCH IS REALLY
INTO ASTROLOGY.

10:14.655 --> 10:17.033
- ASTROLOGY.
- MM.

10:17.116 --> 10:21.203
ALSO--THIS IS GONNA SOUND
KIND OF WEIRD.

10:21.287 --> 10:23.748
HE LOVES BABY TALK.
HE FINDS IT SEXY.

10:23.831 --> 10:25.541
- HE REALLY LOVES IT?

10:25.625 --> 10:28.419
- HE "WEA-WY WOVES" IT.

10:31.088 --> 10:33.382
- [playing bright music]

10:33.466 --> 10:37.178
- YOU'RE AMAZING.
I HAD NO IDEA.

10:37.261 --> 10:38.512
♪ ♪

10:38.596 --> 10:39.513
- [sneezes]

10:39.597 --> 10:40.389
- BLESS YOU.

10:40.473 --> 10:42.475
- THANKS.

10:48.481 --> 10:51.525
- VICTORIA,
A PLAYER PIANO?

10:51.609 --> 10:53.694
UNLESS J.J.'S AN IDIOT,
HE'S NEVER GONNA FALL FOR THAT.

10:53.778 --> 10:57.198
- WELL, YOU FELL FOR IT.

10:57.281 --> 10:59.617
- I'M VERY TRUSTING.

10:59.700 --> 11:01.243
SO WHAT'S J.J. LIKE?

11:01.327 --> 11:03.579
- WELL, HE'S ACTUALLY
KIND OF BRILLIANT

11:03.662 --> 11:07.041
IN A GRUFF,
DIAMOND-IN-THE-ROUGH WAY.

11:07.124 --> 11:09.126
I'M ODDLY TAKEN WITH HIM.

11:09.210 --> 11:11.754
THAT'S WHY I BOUGHT
THE PLAYER PIANO.

11:11.837 --> 11:15.383
HE MAKES ME WANT TO APPEAR TO BE
A BETTER PERSON.

11:15.466 --> 11:17.218
[doorbell chimes]

11:19.512 --> 11:21.347
HI, J.J.
- VICTORIA, I'M IN SHOCK.

11:21.430 --> 11:23.140
I HEARD YOU PLAYING
WALKING UP THE STREET.

11:23.224 --> 11:24.934
IT SOUNDED BEAUTIFUL.
- AW, THANKS.

11:25.017 --> 11:26.936
YOU KNOW, PLAYING THE PIANO'S
KIND OF LIKE RIDING A BIKE.

11:27.019 --> 11:28.938
ONCE YOU LEARN,
YOU NEVER FORGET.

11:29.021 --> 11:32.733
- EVERYBODY HOLD STILL.
THE CRICKET'S ON THE PIANO.

11:32.817 --> 11:35.736
[music playing]

11:35.820 --> 11:39.782
♪ ♪

11:39.865 --> 11:42.618
- ALSO, I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO RIDE A BIKE.

11:45.830 --> 11:48.124
- SO WHAT DID JOY TELL YOU?

11:48.207 --> 11:51.544
- WELL, SHE LIKES A MAN
TO SMELL LIKE A MAN,

11:51.627 --> 11:54.338
SO DON'T SHOWER
FOR A FEW DAYS.

11:54.422 --> 11:57.007
GET RIPE.

11:57.091 --> 11:59.009
- YOU SURE?
- THAT'S WHAT SHE SAID.

11:59.093 --> 12:03.264
AND SHE WANTS A GUY
THAT LOVES SPORTS.

12:03.347 --> 12:06.350
AND BE FRUGAL.
SHE ADMIRES A PENNY PINCHER.

12:06.434 --> 12:08.602
- BUT THIS IS ALL SO DIFFERENT
THAN THE WAY SHE'S SEEN ME ACT.

12:08.686 --> 12:09.812
- SO?

12:09.895 --> 12:11.272
YOU TELL HER
YOU HAVE A WORK SELF

12:11.355 --> 12:12.815
AND A TRUE SELF.

12:12.898 --> 12:14.233
NOW, GO GET STINKY.

12:14.316 --> 12:17.987
- YES, FOR JOY.

12:18.070 --> 12:20.698
- [playing graceful melody
off-key]

12:20.781 --> 12:28.831
♪ ♪

12:31.792 --> 12:35.045
- YOU'RE GETTING THERE, KID.
LET'S DO IT AGAIN.

12:35.129 --> 12:38.466
- NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
NO MORE PRACTICING.

12:38.549 --> 12:40.676
I KNOW.
LET'S GO TO DINNER.

12:40.759 --> 12:42.511
- YOU'RE HUNGRY?

12:42.595 --> 12:47.057
- WELL, I COULD SNIFF
SOME CHINESE.

12:47.141 --> 12:48.851
WE COULD SWING BY YOUR PLACE,
SO YOU COULD CHANGE.

12:48.934 --> 12:50.311
I'M SURE
IT WAS JUST AN OVERSIGHT,

12:50.394 --> 12:54.023
BUT YOU'RE WEARING A BROWN BELT
AND BLACK SHOES.

12:54.106 --> 12:56.525
- MY MOST COMFORTABLE BELT
WITH MY MOST COMFORTABLE SHOES.

12:56.609 --> 12:59.028
- ALL RIGHT,
WELL, THAT'S A SLIPPERY SLOPE.

12:59.111 --> 13:00.863
I MEAN, ONCE YOU START DRESSING
FOR COMFORT,

13:00.946 --> 13:04.742
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,
YOU'LL BE EATING FOR PLEASURE.

13:04.825 --> 13:06.202
- I ALWAYS EAT
FOR PLEASURE.

13:06.285 --> 13:08.913
- WELL, I HAVEN'T DONE THAT
SINCE THE '80s.

13:08.996 --> 13:10.247
- I CAN HONESTLY SAY

13:10.331 --> 13:12.583
I HAVE NEVER MET A WOMAN
LIKE YOU.

13:12.666 --> 13:16.378
- THANK YOU.

13:16.462 --> 13:17.880
YOU KNOW,
WHEN YOU GO TO HOLLYWOOD,

13:17.963 --> 13:19.381
YOU'RE GONNA MEET
A LOT OF PEOPLE LIKE ME.

13:19.465 --> 13:20.883
- I'D NEVER LEAVE CLEVELAND.

13:20.966 --> 13:24.136
MY MEMORIES WITH MY LATE WIFE
ARE HERE.

13:24.220 --> 13:27.848
THIS MOVIE
IS MY LAST LOVE LETTER TO HER.

13:27.932 --> 13:31.352
- THAT MUST BE WHY
IT TOUCHED ME SO WHEN I READ IT.

13:31.435 --> 13:32.853
YOU MUST MISS HER TERRIBLY.

13:32.937 --> 13:35.397
I KNOW
I MISS MY HUSBAND.

13:35.481 --> 13:38.567
- THE WORST TIME FOR ME
IS WAKING UP.

13:38.651 --> 13:40.736
IT'S THAT BRIEF MOMENT
JUST BEFORE YOU'RE CONSCIOUS

13:40.819 --> 13:43.113
WHEN YOU FORGET.

13:43.197 --> 13:44.406
- YEAH,
I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

13:44.490 --> 13:47.910
I REACH OVER FOR EMMET AND--

13:47.993 --> 13:50.412
AND THE MOMENT
IS GONE.

13:50.496 --> 13:52.831
- NICE TO TALK ABOUT THIS
WITH SOMEONE WHO KNOWS.

13:52.915 --> 13:55.209
- YEAH, IT IS.

13:55.292 --> 13:57.127
SO THERE HASN'T BEEN
ANYONE SINCE--

13:57.211 --> 13:59.880
- NO, NO, NO.
I DON'T DATE.

13:59.964 --> 14:01.590
- BUT WHAT IF,

14:01.674 --> 14:05.135
OH, LIKE, YOU MET THIS AMAZING,
BEAUTIFUL WOMAN

14:05.219 --> 14:06.804
WHO WAS WILLING
TO OVERLOOK YOUR FLAWS?

14:06.887 --> 14:12.101
YOU KNOW,
ONCE YOU FIXED A FEW THINGS.

14:12.184 --> 14:14.562
- NO, I'D BE FLATTERED,

14:14.645 --> 14:16.939
BUT I GOT IT RIGHT
THE FIRST TIME.

14:17.022 --> 14:20.442
- WELL, SHE WAS A VERY LUCKY
WOMAN TO HAVE HAD YOU.

14:20.526 --> 14:22.403
- AH.

14:22.486 --> 14:24.238
- OH, DEAR LORD.

14:29.660 --> 14:32.371
- THIS IS GREAT, RIGHT?
GOING OUT TO DINNER AFTER WORK.

14:32.454 --> 14:34.456
GIVES US A CHANCE TO GO
FROM OUR WORK SELVES

14:34.540 --> 14:36.417
TO OUR TRUE SELVES.

14:36.500 --> 14:38.836
- YES, TO OUR TRUE SELVES.

14:38.919 --> 14:41.213
- HOPE YOU DON'T MIND EATING
AT 4:30.

14:41.297 --> 14:42.631
EARLY BIRD SPECIAL.

14:42.715 --> 14:45.634
ALSO, I BROUGHT US
OUR OWN APPETIZERS.

14:45.718 --> 14:48.762
THAT'S WHERE THEY GET YOU.

14:48.846 --> 14:49.972
MUSHROOM CAP?

14:50.055 --> 14:54.268
- THANKS, BUT I WONDER IF THOSE
MIGHT NOT HAVE TAKEN A TURN.

14:54.351 --> 14:55.936
- OH, THAT'S NOT THE MUSHROOMS
YOU'RE SMELLING.

14:56.020 --> 14:58.647
THAT'S ALL ME, BABY.

14:58.731 --> 15:00.482
I BELIEVE A MAN
SHOULD SMELL LIKE A MAN.

15:00.566 --> 15:02.610
I HAVEN'T TAKEN A SHOWER
IN DAYS.

15:02.693 --> 15:06.655
ALSO SAVES
ON THE WATER BILL.

15:06.739 --> 15:10.159
- SO "FWUGAL."

15:10.242 --> 15:13.495
SOUNDS "WIKE" SOMEBODY
IS A "SAGITTAWIUS."

15:16.373 --> 15:18.334
- OH, YOU'RE INTO ASTROLOGY.

15:18.417 --> 15:20.711
- YES, I'M A "TAUWUS."

15:20.794 --> 15:24.548
DON'T SHOW ME "WED."

15:27.760 --> 15:29.511
- HEY, ABOUT THOSE BROWNS?

15:29.595 --> 15:32.222
- OH, YOU LIKE THE BROWNS,
DO YOU?

15:32.306 --> 15:33.849
- ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
I LIVE AND BREATHE 'EM.

15:33.932 --> 15:35.726
I'M EVEN THINKING
ABOUT GETTING SEASON TICKETS

15:35.809 --> 15:37.019
IN THE DAWG POUND.

15:37.102 --> 15:38.687
WE COULD PAINT OUR FACES
AND GO EVERY SUNDAY.

15:38.771 --> 15:42.066
[barks]

15:42.149 --> 15:43.567
- HE SMELLS BAD,

15:43.651 --> 15:45.694
AND I'M MAKING A COMPLETE FOOL
OF MYSELF.

15:45.778 --> 15:49.031
- ONE OF THOSE THINGS
I CAN'T BELIEVE.

15:50.616 --> 15:52.409
- I BETTER GET BACK.

15:52.493 --> 15:54.328
WAIT A MINUTE
AND CALL MY CELL.

15:54.411 --> 15:56.413
PRETEND IT'S AN EMERGENCY,
SO I HAVE TO LEAVE.

15:56.497 --> 15:58.165
- OH, HONEY, HE'S GONNA SEE
RIGHT THROUGH THAT TRICK.

15:58.248 --> 15:59.541
- JOY, THERE'S BEEN
AN EMERGENCY.

15:59.625 --> 16:03.170
I HAVE TO LEAVE.

16:10.511 --> 16:12.721
- OH, THANKS FOR COMING, J.J.

16:12.805 --> 16:15.724
HEY, YOUR BELT
MATCHES YOUR SHOES.

16:15.808 --> 16:17.851
- IT HAPPENS
EVERY NOW AND THEN.

16:17.935 --> 16:19.228
- [laughs]

16:19.311 --> 16:22.231
- I'M EXCITED
TO BID ON JOY'S EYEBROW SHAPING.

16:22.314 --> 16:24.108
- OH, WELL, GOOD.

16:25.359 --> 16:27.027
- I WAS JOKING.

16:27.111 --> 16:29.780
- AS WAS I.

16:29.863 --> 16:31.573
- ELKA, WHY DID YOU INVITE
ONLY MEN?

16:31.657 --> 16:33.075
NO ONE'S BIDDING
ON ANYTHING.

16:33.158 --> 16:34.910
- WELL, I'VE GOT
A FEW OLD THINGS

16:34.993 --> 16:36.912
THAT I THINK
THEY MIGHT LIKE.

16:36.995 --> 16:39.081
- OKAY, WELL,
I'LL GET THEIR ATTENTION.

16:39.164 --> 16:40.916
[glass clinks]

16:40.999 --> 16:45.295
- IT'S TIME TO SAY THANK YOU
TO THREE SPECIAL WOMEN.

16:45.379 --> 16:46.755
COME ON UP, GIRLS.

16:46.839 --> 16:49.591
[applause]

16:49.675 --> 16:50.718
- THANK YOU.

16:50.801 --> 16:52.219
WE'RE ALWAYS READY
TO DO OUR PART

16:52.302 --> 16:54.096
FOR ELKA'S CAMPAIGN.
- GOOD.

16:54.179 --> 16:56.890
LET'S STARTING THE BIDDING
WITH MELANIE.

16:56.974 --> 16:58.308
- BIDDING?

16:58.392 --> 17:02.062
- WHO WOULD GIVE ME 200
FOR THIS UNINHIBITED BEAUTY?

17:02.146 --> 17:04.940
- ELKA, I AM NOT A PIECE OF--
- $1,000.

17:05.022 --> 17:09.153
- 1,000, REALLY?
WOW.

17:09.236 --> 17:10.570
- AND LIKE YOU SAID
IN THE EMAIL,

17:10.654 --> 17:12.406
NO TABOOS, RIGHT?

17:12.489 --> 17:14.782
- WHAT?
OH, NO, THERE ARE TABOOS.

17:14.867 --> 17:16.160
- GET OFF THE BLOCK.
YOU'RE SOLD.

17:16.242 --> 17:18.912
- [stammers]

17:18.996 --> 17:20.830
- I HAVE A DATE.

17:20.914 --> 17:22.583
MOTHER'S GONNA HAVE
TO GET HERSELF OUT OF THE TUB

17:22.665 --> 17:24.667
SATURDAY NIGHT.

17:29.006 --> 17:34.136
- NEXT UP ON <i> ANTIQUES ROADSHOW,</i>
VICTORIA CHASE.

17:34.219 --> 17:35.637
- I BID 5,000.

17:35.721 --> 17:38.474
- OH, J.J., THAT'S SO SWEET.

17:38.557 --> 17:40.309
- ANYONE HERE WANT TO BID
AGAINST ME?

17:40.392 --> 17:42.811
PUT YOUR ARM DOWN.

17:44.146 --> 17:46.440
- SOLD TO THE MAN
WHO DOESN'T KNOW

17:46.523 --> 17:48.400
WHAT HE'S GETTING INTO.

17:50.527 --> 17:52.821
- OH, J.J., YOU DIDN'T HAVE
TO SPEND ALL THAT.

17:52.905 --> 17:54.156
YOU COULD'VE
JUST ASKED ME OUT.

17:54.239 --> 17:54.990
- IT'S NOT A DATE.

17:55.073 --> 17:57.493
I PAID FOR FIVE HOURS
OF YOUR TIME.

17:57.576 --> 17:58.869
- THEN WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

17:58.952 --> 18:02.372
- YOU'RE GOING
TO PRACTICE.

18:02.456 --> 18:03.707
- OH.

18:03.791 --> 18:06.960
- BUT MAYBE
WE COULD HAVE DINNER FIRST.

18:07.044 --> 18:09.880
- I'D LIKE THAT.
- ME TOO.

18:09.963 --> 18:13.091
- SO IT IS A DATE?
- I GUESS IT IS.

18:13.175 --> 18:15.302
- WELL...

18:15.385 --> 18:18.806
- NOW, I'VE SAVED THE LAST
FOR LAST.

18:23.936 --> 18:26.855
DO I HEAR A QUARTER?

18:26.939 --> 18:28.816
- JOY.

18:28.899 --> 18:31.026
MITCH MAY NOT APPRECIATE YOU,
BUT I DO.

18:31.109 --> 18:33.195
$2,000.

18:33.278 --> 18:35.197
- GOING...

18:35.280 --> 18:36.198
GOING...

18:36.281 --> 18:38.200
- 3,000.

18:38.283 --> 18:39.368
- MITCH?

18:39.451 --> 18:41.745
- JOY, THAT WASN'T US
LAST NIGHT.

18:41.829 --> 18:42.663
HE PLAYED US.

18:42.746 --> 18:45.165
HE TOLD ME TO BE SOMEONE
THAT I'M NOT,

18:45.249 --> 18:47.626
AND I'M GUESSING HE TOLD YOU
TO BE SOMEONE YOU'RE NOT TOO.

18:47.709 --> 18:49.545
- SHE'S WAY OUT OF YOUR LEAGUE,
DUDE. 4,000.

18:49.628 --> 18:50.712
- YOU WANTED HER ALL ALONG.

18:50.796 --> 18:51.964
5,000.

18:52.047 --> 18:53.507
- BECAUSE I'M BETTER FOR HER
THAN YOU.

18:53.590 --> 18:56.176
6,000.
- LOOK, JOY.

18:56.260 --> 18:58.554
I SMELL REALLY GOOD,

18:58.637 --> 19:01.223
AND I WASTE MONEY LIKE CRAZY.

19:01.306 --> 19:02.724
- YOU DO?

19:02.808 --> 19:06.562
AND I DON'T TALK BABY TALK,
AND I HATE ASTROLOGY.

19:06.645 --> 19:10.065
- I'VE BEEN A BLIND FOOL.
- YES, YOU HAVE.

19:10.148 --> 19:12.526
- YOU'RE EVERYTHING
THAT I WANT AND MORE.

19:12.609 --> 19:14.444
- I AM?

19:14.528 --> 19:16.905
- $10,000,
AND THE DATE STARTS RIGHT NOW.

19:21.535 --> 19:23.412
- WHERE ARE WE GOING?
- NOT FAR.

19:23.495 --> 19:26.748
YOU WEIGH A LITTLE MORE
THAN I THOUGHT.

19:29.543 --> 19:32.296
- I HATE THE GUY,
BUT I KIND OF WISH BAZ WAS HERE

19:32.379 --> 19:33.505
TO TELL ME
WHAT TO SAY TO YOU.

19:33.589 --> 19:36.550
- MAYBE YOU DON'T NEED
TO SAY ANYTHING.

19:36.633 --> 19:41.054
- OKAY.
BUT I DO NEED TO KISS YOU.

19:45.267 --> 19:47.269
YOUR LIPS
ARE REALLY SOFT.

19:47.352 --> 19:50.230
- YOU SHOULD FEEL
MY ELBOWS.

19:52.524 --> 19:56.028
- WHAT?
- NEVER MIND.

19:57.696 --> 19:59.781
- OH, THERE YOU ARE.
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

19:59.865 --> 20:03.785
I FOUND SOMETHING IN YOUR SHOWER
THAT I'D LIKE TO KEEP.

20:03.869 --> 20:04.786
- REALLY?

20:04.870 --> 20:06.622
[cricket chirps]
OH!

20:06.705 --> 20:08.290
YOU CAUGHT THE CRICKET.
- YES.

20:08.373 --> 20:10.792
IT'S A VERY RARE
<i>TELEOGRYLLUS MITRATUS.</i>

20:10.876 --> 20:12.294
I'M AN ENTOMOLOGIST.

20:12.377 --> 20:15.464
I HAVE A LIVE FEMALE IN MY LAB
READY TO MATE.

20:15.547 --> 20:17.174
THE FEMALE
HAS NO SEX ORGAN,

20:17.257 --> 20:20.594
SO THE MALE MUST USE
HIS SHARP, BARBED PENIS

20:20.677 --> 20:22.888
TO SAW
THROUGH HER CARAPACE.

20:24.848 --> 20:26.850
WE'LL WATCH IT TOGETHER.

20:33.732 --> 20:34.816
[upbeat music]

20:34.900 --> 20:37.319
- ♪ BA-BA, BA-BA ♪

20:37.402 --> 20:39.571
♪ BA-BA, BA-BA ♪

